node.text:
A psychedelic journey without integration is just a trip to the circus. Who cares what visions you had, or the realms you explored. Did it change your life for the better? This is the litmus test to determine whether a journey was worth it or not. 

My own psychedelic explorations have made me who I am today. They have impacted my work, my romantic life, and my physical health for the better. But they have only done so because I have integrated them into my life. 

I am not recommending anyone take the psychedelic path, that is an absolutely personal choice. But if you feel called, this iss my best advice for integrating your psychedelic journey. 

#psychedelics #psychedelicintegration #cosmicexplorer

Contrary to popular opinion, making money doing what you love is absolutely possible. When you’re doing what you love professionally, is it really “work”? 

One of the most effective ways I’ve found to make this a reality is by harnessing the Da Vinci effect; combining 2 or more of your passions to create a niche. When people can see and feel your love for your work, it naturally draws their curiosity out of them to explore what it is you’re offering.
 
#dowhatyoulove #entrepreneurship #abundancemindset

node.text:
There is a version of you waiting to be accessed in the quantum realm of possibility. 

This version of you is more physically fit. More mentally equipped. More spiritually connected. More financially stable. More romantically fulfilled. It is a version of you that no longer feels alone, that feels connected to a living tribe of travelers on the Way. 

To become this future you, requires a simple choice. Say yes. The Fit For Service Fellowship will take care of the rest. This isn’t an empty boast, these are the words of the members themselves. In a survey 100% of all members said the following:

I experienced transformational growth.
I formed lifelong friendships. 
I feel more fit for service.
I would recommend it to friends and family. 

On top of that close to half of the members formed some new business endeavor, either on their own or with another member. 

The applications to join for the final trimester of the year are open now. The online programming begins in September and in October we are going to Sedona to meet with some of my own greatest teachers - to help us awaken the twin dragons of our masculine and feminine potential. If you are called, please apply. I look forward to meeting you in a few months!

LINK IN BIO

#fitforservicefellowship #fitforservice #community

node.text:
A psychedelic journey without integration is just a trip to the circus. Who cares what visions you had, or the realms you explored. Did it change your life for the better? This is the litmus test to determine whether a journey was worth it or not. 

My own psychedelic explorations have made me who I am today. They have impacted my work, my romantic life, and my physical health for the better. But they have only done so because I have integrated them into my life. 

I am not recommending anyone take the psychedelic path, that is an absolutely personal choice. But if you feel called, this iss my best advice for integrating your psychedelic journey. 

#psychedelics #psychedelicintegration #cosmicexplorer

node.text:
It’s as if we have a fetish for self punishment. Mentally traumatizing ourself about something we did in the past, to prevent it from happening in the future. 

This type of punishment isn’t even the best way to train a dog, or a horse. Let alone a human. The carrot, or the little biscuit and some encouragement is the best way to train any mammal, long term. Otherwise you get an animal who is filled with fear, shy and nervous.

So train yourself the same way. 

Reward your positive behaviors and forgive your mistakes immediately upon learning the lesson. I wish my basketball coach would have done it that way. But more importantly, I can start doing it that way, because part of the reason I am writing this is that I caught myself living in the past and beating myself up for “not doing more.” 

Well fuck that, for myself and all of you. All we have is now. Hoka ✊

#bepresent #beherenow #letgo

node.text:
Contrary to popular opinion, making money doing what you love is absolutely possible. When you’re doing what you love professionally, is it really “work”? 

One of the most effective ways I’ve found to make this a reality is by harnessing the Da Vinci effect; combining 2 or more of your passions to create a niche. When people can see and feel your love for your work, it naturally draws their curiosity out of them to explore what it is you’re offering.
 
#dowhatyoulove #entrepreneurship #abundancemindset

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '2 "EXPOSE YOURSELF TO YOUR DEEPEST FEAR; AFTER THAT, FEAR HAS NO POWER, AND THE FEAR OF FREEDOM SHRINKS AND VANISHES. YOU ARE FREE." -JIM MORRISON A'.

node.text:
We are so scared of our Fear. Not actual danger, but our Fear. Why? 

Fear is our greatest teacher, and one of our greatest allies. It points our way toward the work we have to do and the challenges we have to overcome. 

I get it though, it's hell confronting our fear. But you know what else is hell? A really hard workout. Building a business. Forty minutes in a sauna. Three minutes of cold. 

And when you overcome any one of those things, you get a little stronger, a little better, and a little more free... from Fear. 

Artist Unknown

#fearquotes #faceyourfear #challengeaccepted

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas. May be an image of text that says 'Aubrey Marcus @AubreyMarcus The moment you base your confidence on your function, rather than your essence, you are lost in a nightmare of anxiety. Functions can be replaced. No matter what you "do" someone can "do" it better. Except be you. So let your confidence rest in your essence, not function.'.

node.text:
Someone can do your job better. Someone can do your lover better. Someone is more famous, and more wealthy than you. 

But they can NEVER be you. And you are amazing. Unique in the absolute sense of the word. How cool is that? 

You can’t be replicated and never will be. And if you’re gonna tell me about clones right now I don’t want to hear it. I have identical twin sisters and they couldn’t be more different. That’s rad! That’s perfect. 

Trust in your you. 

Someone is gonna love you for that, hire you for that and befriend you for that. That is why your essence is so much more important than your function. 

Now that doesn’t mean that you shouldn’t bust your ass to get better and do cool shit. Just don’t do it to be someone else, do it because it is an expression of who you are, what you are, and how you serve 💙

#beyourselfquotes #individuality #trustyourself

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas with @markmanson. May be an image of text that says 'THE DESIRE FOR MORE POSITIVE EXPERIENCE IS ITSELF A NEGATIVE EXPERIENCE. AND, PARADOXICALLY, THE ACCEPTANCE OF ONE'S NEGATIVE EXPERIENCE IS ITSELF A POSITIVE EXPERIENCE. -MARK MANSON A'.

node.text:
This is the most profound teaching that rests at the cornerstone of the pursuit of happiness.

Amor Fati. Love what is. 

Not what might be, or what could be, or what should be... what is. 

#acceptance #love #perspectivequotes
